{{Infobox college | name = China Evangelical Seminary | native_name = 中華福音神學院 | image_name = | caption = | established = 1970 | religious_affiliation = [[Evangelical]] | location = 101 Ting Chou Road, Sec 3, Taipei, Taiwan ROC | website = http://www.ces.org.tw }} '''China Evangelical Seminary''' ({{zh|t=中華福音神學院|p=Zhōnghuá Fúyīn Shénxué yuàn}} or {{zh|t=華神|p=Huá Shén}}) is a private [[evangelical]] [[seminary]] based in [[Taipei]], [[Taiwan]].
== History == China Evangelical Seminary was established in 1970 by [[James Hudson Taylor III]]. As founding president, Taylor saw the seminary as an institution to train university graduates in theological education.<ref name="Rubinstein1991">{{cite book|last=Rubinstein|first=Murray A. |title=The Protestant Community on Modern Taiwan: Mission, Seminary, and Church|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rNanwYnPdPQC&pg=PA95|year=1991|publisher=M.E. Sharpe|location=Armonk, NY|isbn=978-0-87332-658-2|pages=95-116}}</ref>
In 1979, upon receiving an invitation to serve as general director of [[Overseas Missionary Fellowship]], Taylor recommended to the seminary board to appoint a Chinese to lead the seminary.<ref>{{cite BDCC|url-id=james-hudson-taylor-iii|title=James Hudson Taylor III (1929—2009)|first=Mark S.|last=Bradley|access-date=11 June 2018}}</ref> From 1980 to 1990, the seminary president was [[Timothy Lin]], who also taught Old Testament and Pastoral Ministry.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/latimes/obituary.aspx?n=timothy-lin&pid=134661585|title=Dr. Timothy Lin's Obituary|last=|first=|date=20 October 2009|website=Los Angeles Times|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=28 January 2018}}</ref>
In 1986, an extension campus was established in the Los Angeles suburb of [[Monterey Park, California|Monterey Park]], which is now known as the China Evangelical Seminary North America. This extension became independent in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cesna.edu/en/home-en/about-cesna/cesna-history.html|publisher=China Evangelical Seminary North America|title=About CESNA|access-date=28 January 2018}}</ref>
== Academics == The seminary is accredited by the [[Asia Theological Association]] and currently offers the following degrees:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ataasia.com/members/china-evangelical-seminary/|publisher=Asia Theological Association|title=China Evangelical Seminary|access-date=28 January 2018}}</ref> * Diploma in Christian Studies * Master of Divinity * Master of Arts in Religion * Master of Christian Studies * Master of Theology * Doctor of Ministry
