'''''Invisible Eagle - The History Of Nazi Occultism''''' is a book written by [[Alan Baker (historian)|Alan Baker]]. It was published in 2000 by [[Virgin Books]].<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/invisible-eagle-alan-baker/1005345721?ean=9781852278632 |title=Invisible Eagle: The History of Nazi Occultism by Alan Baker &#124; 9781852278632 &#124; Hardcover &#124; Barnes & Noble |publisher=Barnesandnoble.com |date= |accessdate=2015-06-17}}</ref> Among other subjects the book deals with themes of [[Hollow Earth]] theory, [[Welteislehre]], [[foo fighters]], [[Vril Society]] and similar speculative theories that were associated with the [[Third Reich]].

