{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}} {{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}} {{Infobox religious biography | honorific-prefix = ''[[Muni (Jainism)|Muni]] Shri'' 108 | honorific-suffix = ''Ji Maharaj'' | image = Muni Shri Pramansagar Ji.jpg | alt = Pramansagar | caption = Muni Pramansagar | religion = [[Jainism]] | sect = ''[[Digambara]]'' | birth_name = Naveen Kumar Jain | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1967|6|27|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Hazaribagh]], [[Jharkhand]] | father = Shri Surendra Kumar Jain | mother = Shrimati Sohni Devi Jain | initiator = ''[[Acharya (Jainism)|Acharya]]'' [[Vidyasagar (Jain monk)|Vidyasagar]] | initiation_place = [[Sonagiri]] | initiation_date = 31 March 1988 | website = [http://www.munipramansagar.net ''Official website''] }} {{Jainism}} '''Muni Pramansagar''' is a ''[[Digambar monk]]'' who took initiative in ''Dharmbachao Andolan'' to oppose the [[High Court]]'s decision to ban ''[[Sallekhana]]''. He called for a massive gathering of 1 [[crore]] community members to celebrate the [[Supreme court|Supreme Court]]'s order staying the ban on ''Sallekhana'' by chanting 1 crore hymns. Gunayatan is one of his other religious initiatives. His pravachans and ''Shanka Samadhan'' programme are aired on [[Jinvani channel]] as ''Santvani ,Paras Channel respectively''
== Life == Pramansagar was born on 27 June 1967 in [[Hazaribagh]], [[Jharkhand]] as Naveen Kumar Jain.<ref>{{citation |title=Muni Shri 108 Praman Sagar Ji Maharaj |url=http://jainmunilocator.org/munis.php?id=44 |work=Jain Muni Locator }}</ref> His parents Surendra Kumar Jain and Sohni Devi Jain live near Bengali Durga Mandap.<ref>{{citation |last=Jaipuriar |first=Vishvendu | title=Jumbo chariot cheer amid ‘holy’ rain |url=http://www.telegraphindia.com/1130531/jsp/jharkhand/story_16955686.jsp#.Vfo-6qC3TqA |publisher=[[The Telegraph (Calcutta)|The Telegraph]] |location=[[Hazaribagh]] |date=30 May 2013 }}</ref> He got ''Vairagya'' on 4 March 1984 and was initiated as a ''[[Digambara monk]]'' by ''[[Acharya (Jainism)|Acharya]]'' [[Vidyasagar (Jain monk)|Vidyasagar]] on 31 March 1988 in [[Sonagiri]].<ref>{{citation |url=http://m.timesofindia.com/articleshow/6823669.cms |title=Jain Muni Pramansagar ji Maharaj disciple of Acharya Vidyasagar ji Maharaj would discourse on Ramayana and Geeta at the local Zila school ground from November 7 to 11. The four day programme being organised by Vishwa Dharma Jagaran Manch is expected to garner huge crowd in wake of the popularity that Maharaj has gained while giving similar discourse in other cities of the country. |work=[[The Times of India]] |date=27 October 2010 }}</ref> On the issue of ''[[Sallekhana]]'' controversy, he said {{quote|''Santhara'' is not a suicide. Jainism considers suicide a sin. Followers of every religion do penance through different means and Jainism also does so for self-purification.<ref>{{citation |last=Staff |first=Pratika |title=Fatal blow: why the Jain practice of voluntary death is a crime |url=http://www.catchnews.com/india-news/fatal-blow-why-the-jain-practice-of-voluntary-death-is-a-crime-1439307604.html |work=Catch News |date=11 August 2015 }}</ref>|''Muni'' Pramansagar}}
''Muni'' Pramansagar is a ''Digambar'' monk who took initiative in ''Dharmbachao Andolan'' to oppose the [[High Court]]'s decision to ban ''Sallekhana''.<ref>{{citation |last=Sharma |first=Lalit |title=Rajasthan high court bans Jain ritual of fasting unto death |url=http://hindustantimes.com/india-topstories/rajasthan-high-court-bans-jain-ritual-of-fasting-unto-death/article1-1378673.aspx |work=[[Hindustan Times]] |date=10 August 2015 |location=[[Jaipur]] }}</ref><ref>{{citation |agency=[[ETV Rajasthan]] |title=Muni Shri Praman Sagar talks about the tradition of Santhara |url=http://news18.com/videos/uttar-pradesh/muni-shri-praman-sagar-talks-about-the-tradition-of-santhara-805639.html |date=13 September 2015 |location=[[Uttar Pradesh]] |work=News18 }}</ref> He called for a massive gathering of 1 crore community members to celebrate the [[Supreme court|Supreme Court]]'s order staying the ban on ''Sallekhana'' by chanting 1 [[crore]] hymns.<ref>{{citation |last=Singh |first=Mahim Pratap |title=Hours after SC ruling, octogenarian ‘resumes’ Santhara in Bikaner |url=http://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-others/hours-after-sc-ruling-octogenarian-resumes-santhara-in-bikaner |work=[[The Indian Express]] |location=[[Jaipur]] |date=1 September 2015 }}</ref> Gunayatan is one of his other religious initiatives. His ''[[pravachan]]s'' and ''Shanka Samadhan'' programme are aired on Jinvani & Parastv channel.<ref>{{citation |title=Programs |url=http://www.jinvanichannel.com/shows.aspx |publisher=[[Jinvani channel]] }}</ref>
He was present in the Lord [[Gommateshwara statue|Bahubali’s statue]] anointment with 1,008 ''[[kalasha]]s''.<ref>{{citation |title=Lord Bahubali’s statue anointed with 1,008 kalashas |url=http://thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/lord-bahubalis-statue-anointed-with-1008-kalashas/article6841658.ece |work=[[The Hindu]] |date=31 January 2015 }}</ref> He visited Kuchaman, [[Rajasthan]] in June 2016.<ref>{{citation |title=दिखावे का भक्ति में कोई स्थान नहीं हैं : मुनि |url=http://bhaskar.com/news/RAJ-OTH-MAT-latest-kuchaman-news-051003-344797-NOR.html |work=[[Dainik Bhaskar]] |date=11 June 2016 }}</ref>
His 2016 Chaturmas was in Vaishali Nagar, [[Ajmer]], [[Rajasthan]].<ref>{{citation |url=http://m.bhaskar.com/news/RAJ-AJM-OMC-MAT-latest-ajmer-news-032003-80629-NOR.html |title=चातुर्मास के लिए बैठक कल |work=[[Dainik Bhaskar]] |date=29 April 2016 }}</ref>
